definitions.definition: A sound produced by the vocal cords with relatively little restriction of the oral cavity , forming the prominent sound of a syllable .
examples: In Welsh, the w usually represents a vowel .

definitions.definition: A letter representing the sound of a vowel; in English, the vowels are a , e , i , o , u , w (sometimes), y (sometimes) .
examples: Facetiously is spelled with all six vowels in alphabetical order.

main_definition: ( phonetics ) A sound produced by the vocal cords with relatively little restriction of the oral cavity , forming the prominent sound of a syllable .
